OL,3,CMan who led an 'angry' group before
OL,4,Ckicking two police officers jailed
OL,6,F"Whereas others such as you," he said,
OL,7,F"decided to usurp this terrible
OL,8,Fincident with an excuse for mindless,
OL,9,Fdrunken thuggery."
OL,11,FHe continued: "You along with hundreds
OL,12,Fof other people were on the streets
OL,13,Fready to cause disorder...
OL,15,F"When you lead a mob and encourage
OL,16,Fthem, and start violence you cannot
OL,17,Fthen seek to cast the blame on
OL,18,Fothers... when you join in mob
OL,19,Fviolence you bear your share for the
OL,20,Fresponsibility of what the mob does."
